modules.description: Constructs a CoHTTP request header and body from a multipart form value, handling proper encoding and boundary generation. Works with `Multipart_form.multipart` values, which represent form data with associated content types and encodings. Useful for client-side HTTP requests that need to upload form data with files or custom content types.

Parses HTTP multipart/form-data requests into a structured tree and a stream of individual parts. Works with Cohttp.Request.t, Cohttp.Header.t, and Cohttp_lwt.Body.t values. Useful for handling file uploads or form submissions where each part's header and content must be processed separately.

This module handles both the construction and parsing of HTTP multipart/form-data requests, enabling seamless client-side form submission and server-side form data extraction. It operates on `multipart` values, request headers, and bodies, providing functions to encode form data with proper boundaries and to decode incoming requests into individual parts. You can use it to upload files from a client by building correctly formatted requests or to process each part of an uploaded form on the server, including headers and content streams.
